are bent and your weight is distributed evenly in your feet.";i:14;s:57:"Your spine is lifted and your arms are extended overhead.";i:15;s:135:"As suggested by its name the pose is a challenging one as it engages your full body particularly your leg muscles and spinal extensors.";i:16;s:116:"Many yoga beginners do not realize that the adductors in your inner thighs are essential for building a strong core.";i:17;s:69:"Work Chair Pose to gain strength in both your core and thigh muscles.";i:18;s:35:"Starting in Mountain pose Tadasana.";i:19;s:93:"Exhale as you bend your knees and move your hips back as if you were sitting down on a chair.";i:20;s:61:"Draw your lower abdomen in and up to support your lower back.";i:21;s:87:"Send your hips back rather than your knees forward so that you can still see your toes.";i:22;s:61:"Inhale as you raise your arms up around your ears and soften.";i:23;s:50:"Yoga Poses Meditations Sequences and Free Classes.";i:24;s:89:"In addition Chair pose is utilized to build integrity in the susceptible Achilles tendon.";i:25;s:100:"As you sit in the pose it gently stretches the tendon allowing the ankle more flexibility and range.";i:26;s:90:"The more strong and open your ankles and feet muscles the more power you will have to run.";i:27;s:81:"This pose will also open your shoulder joints and elongate the side of your body.";i:28;s:83:"The Chair Pose is a yoga exercise that works the butt thighs hamstrings and calves.";i:29;s:38:"It works your body similar to a squat.";i:30;s:52:"Sit as far back as you are comfortable in this pose.";i:31;s:86:"Your aim is to get to the point where you can make a 90 degree angle out of your legs.";i:32;s:41:"Truly Chair pose is a total body workout.";i:33;s:60:"Initially notice how the muscles in your feet and legs feel.";i:34;s:57:"As your pelvis rotates out notice how your core responds.";i:35;s:103:"When your arms lift feel your muscles work to reach your arms overhead while keeping broad collarbones.";i:36;s:23:"Benefits of Chair Pose.";i:37;s:91:"Chair pose has proven to strengthen the muscles especially when it comes to the lower body.";i:38;s:101:"Squatting in general has tremendous benefits for the whole body and helps to improve overall fitness.";i:39;s:37:"Added benefits of chair pose include.";i:40;s:47:"Strengthens the ankles thighs calves and spine.";i:41;s:30:"Stretches shoulders and chest.";i:42;s:105:"Utkatasana or Chair pose strengthens the entire legs from the glutes and thighs to the calves and ankles.";i:43;s:92:"So if youre tired of squatting at the gym you can train your quadriceps with this yoga pose.";i:44;s:113:"Provided that you understand proper Chair pose alignment it is a great pose for practitioners with knee problems.";i:45;s:78:"By building strength in the quads youre strengthening the major supporters of.";i:46;s:145:"Do you see that in traditional chair pose the knees track forward of the ankles and the emphasis is on moving the whole body lower to the ground.";i:47;s:100:"If your knees are forward of your ankles the quads not the glutes are the main muscle group working.";i:48;s:97:"Join our FREE 7-Day Beginners Yoga Challenge Receive a FREE GIFT Previously Members-Only Workout.";i:49;s:39:"Head Neck Essentials httpsshrtlnkco8eq.";i:50;s:30:"Common Mistakes in Chair Pose.";i:51;s:70:"There are two major things I look out for when Im teaching chair pose.";i:52;s:27:"The first is the sway back.";i:53;s:112:"There are certainly times when its good to arch the back catcow pose Im lookin at you but this isnt one of them.";i:54;s:83:"In this instance you could risk low back injury due to compression in the spine so.";i:55;s:386:"In this video we explore the alignment of the pelvis spine and knees in parivrtta utkatasana revolved chair poseWe revisit some of the themes presented in other recent videos that weve posted about rotated postures eg the benefits of maintaining a neutral spine and allowing the pelvis to follow the lumbar spine during twists but with specific cues that pertain to revolved chair pose.";i:56;s:92:"Revolved chair pose is considered very beneficial for the physical body in a number of ways.";i:57;s:25:"Stretches the lower back.";i:58;s:60:"Strengthens the hip flexors quadriceps and adductor muscles.";i:59;s:41:"Opens the shoulders upper back and chest.";i:60;s:37:"Strengthens and stretches the calves.";i:61;s:36:"Improves proprioception in the feet.";i:62;s:42:"Stimulates the abdominal organs and heart.";i:63;s:100:"It is a good idea to do the Chair Pose after you have finished all the other standing yoga postures.";i:64;s:82:"You can then start with the sitting yoga postures or the lying down yoga postures.";i:65;s:34:"Benefits of Utkatasana Chair Pose.";i:66;s:43:"Exercises the spine hips and chest muscles.";i:67;s:42:"Helps strengthen the lower back and torso.";i:68;s:35:"Tones the thigh ankle leg and knee.";}}